data.chText: 这种急性大脑传染病几乎总是导致死亡。
data.enText: This acute infection of the brain is almost invariably fatal.
This is not invariably the case.

data.chText: 答复无例外地又是：“现在不行！”
data.enText: Invariably the reply came back, ‘Not now!’

tr: without variation or change, in every case

value.def: If something invariably happens or is invariably true, it always happens or is always true.

example.ex: They almost invariably get it wrong...

example.tran: 他们的团队协作总是很好。

example.ex: Invariably, he keeps the refrigerator well stocked.
example.tran: 他总是把冰箱塞得满满的。

gramarinfo.label: ADV with v, ADV with cl/group

value.tran: 不变地;总是;始终如一地
